	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There exist more than one &quot;modified MMC3&quot;. There's TxSROM, which runs CHR A17 out to CIRAM A10, and TQROM, which uses CHR A16 to <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/MMC3_with_CHR_ROM_and_CHR_RAM" class="postlink">switch between a ROM and a RAM</a>. There are multicart variants, which typically get the &quot;game&quot; name. And there are plenty of <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/INES_Mapper_206#Variants" class="postlink">variants on the Namco 108 theme</a>. That's why I'm tempted to keep board names for unusual applications of at least Nintendo ASIC mappers.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


