	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />CPROM, TxSROM, and TQROM get &quot;more specific&quot; names because they have different behavior. But &quot;totally unrelated&quot; is stretching it, as the behavior is a small change to the &quot;parent&quot; board. CPROM is CNROM with a fixed bank, TxSROM is TxROM with CHR A17-controlled nametable mirroring, and TQROM is TxROM with CHR A16 switching between two different memories.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


